            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I would like to share my recent experience with Prime Scholars International School to help parents make an informed decision regarding admissions.\n\n1. Admission Process & Communication\nThe admission process lacked clarity and required multiple follow-ups to obtain basic information.\n\n2. Front-Office Staff Attitude\nThe attitude of the front-office representatives, specifically Ms. Aneetha and Ms. Payal, was highly disappointing. In particular, Ms. Aneetha’s attitude toward parents was extremely bad and unprofessional, which does not reflect the standards expected from an institution of this stature.\n\n3. Overall Impression\nWhile the school infrastructure and academic claims may appear promising, the first point of contact—the front-office team—sets the tone for the parent experience. Unfortunately, my interaction raises serious concerns about the school’s commitment to professionalism and respectful engagement.\n\nRecommendation:\nParents should carefully evaluate not only the academic offerings but also the responsiveness and attitude of the administration before making a decision.\n",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
